## Part 2: Comprehensive Accessibility Audit (3-4 hours)

### Goals
- WCAG AA compliance across all features
- Full keyboard navigation
- Screen reader compatibility
- Focus management
- Color contrast verification

### Tasks

**Task 2.1: Keyboard Navigation Audit (1-2 hours)**

**Test all pages:**
- [ ] Dashboard: Tab through widgets, Enter to interact
- [ ] Kanban: Tab through cards, Enter to open
- [ ] Notes: Tab through sidebar, focus editor
- [ ] Calendar: Arrow keys navigate days/events
- [ ] Settings: Tab through all inputs

**Common Issues:**
```typescript
// Fix focus trap in modals
useEffect(() => {
  const handleKeyDown = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
    if (e.key === 'Escape') {
      onClose();
    }
  };

  document.addEventListener('keydown', handleKeyDown);
  return () => document.removeEventListener('keydown', handleKeyDown);
}, [onClose]);

// Add focus styles
.focus-visible:focus {
  outline: 2px solid var(--accent-blue);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

**Task 2.2: Screen Reader Testing (1 hour)**

**Tools:**
- macOS: VoiceOver (Cmd+F5)
- Windows: NVDA (free)

**Check:**
```typescript
// Add ARIA labels
<button aria-label="Add new task">
  +
</button>

// Add ARIA roles
<div role="alert" aria-live="polite">
  Task added successfully
</div>

// Add ARIA states
<button aria-expanded={isOpen} aria-haspopup="true">
  Menu
</button>
```

**Task 2.3: Color Contrast Verification (1 hour)**

```typescript
// Use WebAIM Contrast Checker
// Verify all text meets 4.5:1 ratio

// Fix low contrast
const colors = {
  // Before: 3:1 (FAIL)
  'text-light-secondary': '#888888',

  // After: 4.6:1 (PASS)
  'text-light-secondary': '#666666',
};
```

